## 11. Infrastructure Health Checks (added 2026-04-25)

**PostgreSQL pg_isready**
- [ ] Run: `pg_isready -U david -d dgsoftwash`
- [ ] Command exits with code 0 (output should say "dgsoftwash:5432 - accepting connections")
- [ ] If it fails: run `brew services list | grep postgresql` to check service status

**iCloud Backup Freshness**
- [ ] Confirm 2TB HDD is mounted: `ls "/Volumes/2TB HDD/Backups/"`
- [ ] Run: `find "/Volumes/2TB HDD/Backups/iCloud Drive" -maxdepth 1 -mmin -1500 | head -5`
- [ ] Command returns at least one file/folder path (backup destination modified within last 25 hours)
- [ ] If empty: check iCloud backup daemon with `sudo launchctl list | grep icloud` (should be present, exit 0)

**Backblaze XML Status**
- [ ] Run: `cat /Library/Backblaze.bzpkg/bzdata/overviewstatus.xml | grep cur_state`
- [ ] Output does NOT contain `cur_state="error"` or `cur_state="stopped"`
- [ ] Run: `cat /Library/Backblaze.bzpkg/bzdata/bzreports/bzdc_synchostinfo.xml | grep bzlicense_status`
- [ ] Output does NOT contain `expired` or `deleted`
- [ ] If license issue: log into backblaze.com (dbemish82@yahoo.com) and verify account status

**DB Backup Freshness (6-hour schedule)**
- [ ] Run: `ls -lt "/Volumes/2TB HDD/Backups/database/" | head -5`
- [ ] Most recent `.sql` or `.dump` file is modified within the last 7 hours
- [ ] Verify backup schedule: `launchctl list | grep database-backup` (should be present)
- [ ] Check last backup run: `cat /tmp/database-backup.log | tail -20`

